		<title>15LOCAL HISTORY KIBWORTH contd</title>
		<content>{THE WINDMILL contd.                   
                                       
  The wooden structure, containing all 
 the corn grinding machinery, sits on  
 top of a circular brick base and can  
 be rotated by hand to allow the wooden
 slatted sails to catch any wind. It   
 took fifteen  children to link hands  
 when stretched around the base.       
    It must have been very hard,       
 dangerous work for the miller and his 
 boy in the noisey, cramped            
 conditions.The Windmill, on Mr Briggs 
 farm, can now be visited by interested
 people.                               
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
